parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire valve stems can cause the tire to suddenly deflate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire suddenly deflates while driving
often without warning
and may cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side. The valve stem may be cracked or ruptured
leading to air leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tire sidewall can cause the tire to suddenly deflate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire suddenly deflates while driving
often without warning
and may cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side. The sidewall of the tire may be bulging or separated from the rim.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Manufacturing Defects
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire due to manufacturing defects can cause the tire to suddenly deflate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire suddenly deflates while driving
often without warning
and may cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side. The tire may have visible signs of damage
such as bulges or cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint delamination and peeling can cause rust, which can lead to structural damage and compromise the vehicle's safety. Additionally, the peeling paint can distract the driver, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Paint peeling
blistering
or bubbling on various parts of the vehicle
including the hood
roof
trunk lid
doors
and rear bumper; exposed metal or primer; rust; distraction while driving due to peeling paint hitting the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake and gas pedals can cause accidental acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Foot slipping from the brake pedal to the gas pedal
causing unintended acceleration; feeling of pedals being too close together.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wind noise and vibration can cause driver distraction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Violent shaking or vibration of the vehicle while driving at high speeds with windows down; feeling of vibration coming from the driver's seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and independently
the accelerator pedal sticks or goes all the way to the floor
the vehicle surges forward or backward
the brake pedal is depressed but the vehicle continues to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Pedal interference can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake and accelerator pedals are too close together
the pedals are not adjustable
the driver's foot can accidentally press both pedals simultaneously
the accelerator pedal is depressed when the brake pedal is intended to be pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Speed control issues can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The speed control system is not working correctly
the throttle is set too high
the vehicle accelerates rapidly and independently
the accelerator pedal moves on its own when the vehicle is put into gear.
